com.i2group.apollo.model.security.transport

Class SecurityTagGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.security.transport.SecurityTagGroup

  • public final class SecurityTagGroup
extends Object
    A container for SecurityTags that also specifies whether (and how many of) the SecurityTags that it contains must be present on Items that use security tagging.
    Since:
    4.0

    • Constructor Detail

      • SecurityTagGroup

        public SecurityTagGroup(String id,
                        String displayName,
                        boolean isMandatory,
                        boolean isMultiple,
                        Collection<SecurityTag> securityTags)
        Constructs a new SecurityTagGroup, initializing all mandatory fields.
        Parameters:
        id - A String containing the identifier of this SecurityTagGroup. The identifier must be unique across all SecurityTagGroups.
        displayName - A String containing a human-readable display name for this SecurityTagGroup.
        isMandatory - true if at least one SecurityTag from this SecurityTagGroup must be present on an Item that uses security tagging; false otherwise.
        isMultiple - true if more than one SecurityTag from this SecurityTagGroup can be present on an Item that uses security tagging; false otherwise.
        securityTags - The SecurityTags that this SecurityTagGroup. contains.
